    [ 14] Europe.CONCEPT.1174
    [ 15] Diagnosis of the contact: Major Fault
    [ 16] (PCU)
    [ 17] During the start up phase, after self
    [ 18] test of PCU, when the life signal from
    [ 19] PCU is being received, this test begins
    [ 20] and TCMS shall manage it:
    [ 21] - TCMS
    [ 22] reads
    [ 23] the
    [ 24] contact:
    [ 25] Major
    [ 26] Failure in closed position (i.e no
    [ 27] failure inside PCU);
    [ 28] - TCMS sends for 6 s to PCU the
    [ 29] command to open (just for test) the
    [ 30] contact: Major Failure.
    [ 31] This test is being carried out only if the
    [ 32] pantograph is in lowered position.
    [ 33] When the "Major Fault" contact test is
    [ 34] on going, if the "Raise pantograph"
    [ 35] switch is active, the raise order should
    [ 36] be delayed to the end of the "Major
    [ 37] Fault" contact test.
    [ 38] Derived Requirement
