>>> [ 13] 3.2.2
    [ 14] Pantograph - Lowering
>>> [ 15] 3.2.2.1
    [ 16] Function Design
>>> [ 17] 3.2.2.1.1 Normal Condition
    [ 18] Lowering of pantograph, the Pantograph will stop collecting line current.
    [ 19] Pantograph will be lowered when line voltage system is being de-activated:
    [ 20] -
    [ 21] by switch “Pantograph down” OR
    [ 22] -
    [ 23] by drivers urgency (“Emergency push button”) push button OR
    [ 24] -
    [ 25] by automatic device due to system change OR
    [ 26] -
    [ 27] in case of critical failures (Pantograph control unit output “pantograph internal major failure” in case of
    [ 28] Pantograph control unit fault or difference in pressure control)
    [ 29] -
    [ 30] at cab deactivation (no parking mode active)
    [ 31] All line circuit breakers are ordered to open before lowering the pantograph except in emergency cases.
>>> [ 32] 3.2.2.1.2 Failure Condition
    [ 33] 1)
    [ 34] Pantograph doesn't lower on order.
    [ 35] 2)
    [ 36] Pantograph is lowered unintentionally.
>>> [ 37] 3.2.2.1.3 Failure Supervision
    [ 38] 1)
    [ 39] Manual lowering via panto-cock.
    [ 40] 2)
    [ 41] The faulty pantograph will be blocked.
>>> [ 42] 3.2.2.2
    [ 43] Requirements
    [ 44] ID
>>> [ 45] 2F_04.01.Zefiro-Europe.TRS.266
    [ 46] Description
    [ 47] Pantograph shall be lowered when line voltage system shall be de-activated
    [ 48] - by switching the selector switch to the down position OR
    [ 49] - by drivers emergency push button OR
    [ 50] - in case of failures.
    [ 51] All line circuit breakers shall be open before lowering the pantograph except in emergency cases.
    [ 52] Safety level
    [ 53] SIL 0
    [ 54] ID
